This article is about the one-year anniversary of the Surfside, Florida tragedy, where a building collapsed and 98 people lost their lives. The author describes the hidden fellowship of loss that exists among those who have experienced such a tragedy. They acknowledge that the pain of losing a loved one never truly fades and that grief can sometimes feel overwhelming. However, they also highlight the moments of grace and resilience that people have found in the face of such devastation. The author expresses gratitude for the community's support, including the first responders, the local residents, and people from across the country who donated and showed kindness. They emphasize the power of love in helping people carry the burden of grief and find moments of joy even amidst sorrow. The article concludes with a message of support and prayers for those affected by the tragedy.